"OK noted. This is an important feature. I want to make sure python3 support works first and I'll do this one.\n\n\nDear developers, \n\nin our project (professor.hepforge.org) we switched from pyminuit to iminuit entirely and are very happy with it. The above mentioned feature would benefit our project as we can often construct the gradient of the function we want to minimise. Cpu time of the minimisation currently limits the application to ~ 10 dimensional parameter spaces so it would be cool to go beyond that. \nDo you have an estimate on whether that MINUIT functionality will be part of iminuit anytime soon?\n\nThanks,\nHolger\n"